A politician dies and goes to Heaven. St. Peter meets him at the Pearly Gates and says, 'Well, you're an interesting case. We're not sure whether to send you to Heaven or Hell. So we've decided to let you spend a day in each before you choose.'

First, the politician goes down to Hell. He finds himself on a beautiful golf course with all his old friends. They drink champagne, eat lobster, and have a wonderful time. 

The next day, he goes to Heaven. He spends the day floating on clouds, playing the harp, and singing with angels. It's peaceful, but a little boring.

At the end of the second day, St. Peter asks, 'So, have you made your decision?'

The politician says, 'I have. As nice as Heaven was, I had a much better time in Hell. I choose Hell.'

St. Peter snaps his fingers, and the politician is suddenly in a desolate wasteland, full of fire and brimstone, with his friends screaming in agony.

'What happened?!' the politician cries out to the Devil. 'Yesterday this was a paradise!'

The Devil grins and says, 'Yesterday we were campaigning. Today, you voted.'

"You must be an engineer," says the balloonist.
